message.content: cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.DC, cs.SY - The paper discusses the architecture and design of a new network for HetVNETs, which involves integrating different access networks coherently to meet various QoS requirements for ITS services. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Cloud-RAN and SDN, which are related to Information Theory (cs.IT), Communication (cs.COMM), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and solutions for the new network, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
